    <abstract>P. 33: "The controversial issue here is the interpretation of "holding the name". The
        original Sanskrit term for "holding" is "manasikara" which means "bearing or pondering in
        mind". According to it, "holding the name"should be more like a meditative nien-fo. However,
        the later Pure Land masters tended to interpret it as invocation of the name (invocational
        nien-fo), an interpretation catered to the "common man" /prthagjana) with inferior spiritual
        potential. </abstract>
